<http://www.utro.ru/news/2005/10/16/486470.shtml>

Botulism in Kazakhstan from dried fish
---------------------------------------------
25 persons have been poisoned by domestically prepared fish in the
Mangistauskaya region in western Kazakhstan. One of them has died,
according to the press service of the Republican Ministry of extreme
situations.
25 persons with food poisoning have been seen at the infectious diseases
hospital of Zhanaozen [a town in the Mangistauskaya region] on Fri 14 Oct
2005. All affected individuals are workers in a single organization, all of
whom the day before had eaten dried fish prepared in a home.
7 victims have been hospitalized with the diagnosis of botulism; one of
these died on 16 Oct 2005; 2 more of these patients are receiving life
support. The 18 others are being seen as out-patients.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The Mangistauskaya region is located in the southwest part of Kazakhstan
and adjoins the Caspian Sea. - Mod.NP]
[It is not clear what symptoms the 18 non-admitted individuals have
manifested. With fish-associated botulism, type E is most prevalent. - Mod.LL]
